From edde13359b759e80dd1d1b447be6bcfa650cf35e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 19:52:32 +0200
Subject: [slayzone] slayzone: Phase 7.2 tabbar webui (wires onto Phase 6.3
 host)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Ports the horizontal tab strip onto chrome://slayzone-tabbar/ — the Phase
6.3 WebUIController already existed as a placeholder; 7.2 swaps its
static HTML for the @slayzone/webui-tabbar Vite bundle and extends the
TabsHost Mojo surface with tab-switch instrumentation.

- chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/tabs.mojom: adds GetActiveTabTiming
  method returning (active_id, activated_at_us). Tabbar JS correlates
  its call-site performance.now() against the timestamp to derive the
  <50ms switch benchmark deferred from Phase 6.
- slayzone_tabs_host.{h,cc}: implements GetActiveTabTiming + captures
  last_activation_tick_ in OnTabStripModelChanged when the active-tab
  changed flag flips.
- slayzone_tabbar_ui.cc: swaps the Phase 6.3 static placeholder body
  for the same bundle-serving pattern as Phase 7.1 statusbar — reads
  --slayzone-webui-bundle-dir/tabbar/dist/ with inline error HTML on
  missing bundle, CSP identical to statusbar.

No new URL host (reuses Phase 6.3 chrome://slayzone-tabbar/), no
binder registry change (ForWebUI<SlayzoneTabbarUI>().Add<TabsHost>()
already registered in Phase 6.3), no SlayzoneBrowserView member
change (tabs_host() already present).
